{"lemma":"كَأَنَّ","slug":"كَأَنَّ","root":"ك.#.ن","root_slug":"ك-_-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/ك-_-ن","pos":null,"pos_camel":"verb_pseudo","paradigm":[{"role":"present_nanana","form":"كَأَنَّ","in_corpus":true,"count":18,"asp":"i","per":"na","gen":"na","num":"na"}],"frequency_in_corpus":18,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"كَأَنَّ","root":"","pos":"P","occurrence_count":9},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["conj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n43163"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%83%D9%8E%D8%A3%D9%8E%D9%86%D9%8E%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"conj","gloss":"as if"},{"pos":"conj","gloss":"as if","examples":[{"text":"فَجَعَلْنَاهَا حَصِيدًا كَأَنْ لَمْ تَغْنَ بِالْأَمْسِ كَذٰلِكَ نُفَصِّلُ الْآيَاتِ لِقَوْمٍ يَتَفَكَّرُونَ","english":"We make it as a harvest, as if it had not flourished yesterday. Thus do We explain in detail the signs for a people who give thought."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From كَ (ka) + أَنَّ (ʔanna)."},"ipa":["/ka.ʔan.na/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n43163","headword_ar":"كَانَ","root":"kwn","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He or it was."},{"kind":"text","text":"A verb of the class called incomplete, ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naAqiSN","text_ar":"نَاقِصٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":") because, with the agent which it comprises, or to which it relates, it cannot constitute a complete proposition; i. e., non-attributive. The other verbs of this class are,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zal~a A^aDoHaY A^amosaY A^aSobaHa SaAra","text_ar":"ظَلَّ اَضْحَى اَمْسَى اَصْبَحَ صَارَ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA daAma maAA@nofak~a maA fatiy^a maAbariHa maA zaAla baAta","text_ar":"مَا دَامَ مَاا@نْفَكَّ مَا فَتِيَ مَابَرِحَ مَا زَالَ بَاتَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layosa","text_ar":"لَيْسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". Each of these governs its noun, or subject, in the nom. case, and its enunciative, or predicate, in the acc. case; as,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna zayodN qaAy^imFA","text_ar":"كَانَ زَيْدٌ قَايِمًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Zeyd was standing."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b2-  (The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":"in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yakuno","text_ar":"يَكُنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the like is often irregularly elided.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna","text_ar":"كَانَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", divested of all signification of time. is often used as a copula. (See De Sacy 's Gr. Ar. i. 196.) So too is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAy^inN","text_ar":"كَايِنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA zayodN","text_ar":"هٰذَا زَيْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA kaAy^inN zayodFA","text_ar":"هٰذَا كَايِنٌ زَيْدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify the same. (Mughnee, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^an~a","text_ar":"اَنَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAna","text_ar":"كَانَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as a complete, i. e., an attributive, verb, see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaSala","text_ar":"حَصَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". in three places."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}